    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>The shotel is a downward-curving sword designed to reach over or around an opponent’s shield. The curve of a shotel’s blade varies from sword to sword, and some models are double-edged, while others are single-edged, with the back edge able to be braced against a shield for additional power. Shotels are particularly useful for hooking mounted combatants and ripping them from their steeds.</em></p>\n<p>You gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls with a shotel against opponents using bucklers, light shields, or heavy shields.</p>",
